In March of the 1999 season, KFF decided to promote Mathare United at the expense of Red Berets. The Forces side appealed and the federation readmitted them before eventually deciding to also retain Mathare in the top league.Several matches were abandoned without being resolved. But the saga surrounding Mumias Sugar stole the show. This is not the first time in this column that I am quoting Georg Wilhelm Friedrich Hegel. The influential 19th century German philosopher is attributed for saying: “We learn from history that we do not learn from history.”
I have written about football administrators seeking leadership positions campaigning on the platform of change, gaining the federation top seat only to revert to the same old, same old modus operandi that had brought the local game down to its knees.



