This group transformed to the Inter-Club Consultative Group (ICCG) that vigorously agitated for transparency from a corrupt and mismanaged KFF. They even threatened to withdraw from the federation.
The ICCG later converted to the Kenyan Premier Football Group (KPFG) that evolved into the Kenyan Premier League (KPL) that brought an admirable and desirable level of professional management of the league until 2020.
The federation eventually got back control of the league this season and it is obvious that history is again repeating itself to the detriment of our game.
Two clubs have been expelled from the league for rightfully demanding disclosure on a league broadcast rights deal unilaterally signed by the FKF president.



